column176:
According to Art. 5 from the Disaster Protection Law (DPL), the disaster protection is achieved by:1. conducting preventive activities;
2. carrying out protection activities;
3. coordination of the actions of the Integrated Rescue System;
4. support and disaster recovery;
5. resource provision;
6. acceptance of aid.

