The Disaster Protection Law and the Ministry of Interior Law - 2006 set up an Integrated Rescue system and regulate:
Establishment of an Integrated Rescue System;
Participation of population, institutions and companies;
Declaring of “state of disaster”, support and recreation;
Functions of the bodies of the Executive authorities and the basic functions, tasks and duties of the employees from Ministry of Interior – Fire Services and Protection of the Population teams;
relief and reconstruction
Disaster Protection Act defines Fire Safety and Protection of the Population DG as a fundamental structures of the INTEGRATED RESCUE SYSTEM in case of major disasters (Art. 22).

